00:03:01.570 --> 00:03:03.150 align:middle line:84%
One of the most
sobering realities

00:03:03.150 --> 00:03:06.510 align:middle line:84%
is when poor people
fall ill, there

00:03:06.510 --> 00:03:09.770 align:middle line:84%
is no government medical
insurance to turn to.

00:03:09.770 --> 00:03:12.540 align:middle line:84%
So in such circumstances,
it is the family

00:03:12.540 --> 00:03:17.780 align:middle line:84%
who is looked to when a major
health condition is diagnosed.

00:03:17.780 --> 00:03:20.930 align:middle line:84%
This is probably why
the life expectancy here

00:03:20.930 --> 00:03:25.910 align:middle line:84%
is 64 years as compared
to 78 in the United States

00:03:25.910 --> 00:03:29.780 align:middle line:90%
and 81 in the United Kingdom.

00:03:29.780 --> 00:03:34.270 align:middle line:10%
>> I have started my career
in the year 1984 as a general

00:03:34.270 --> 00:03:38.990 align:middle line:10%
practitioner after getting
my basic degree that is MDBS.

00:03:38.990 --> 00:03:42.710 align:middle line:10%
I was in a feeling that
this country like India

00:03:42.710 --> 00:03:45.910 align:middle line:10%
needs more general
practitioners, not

00:03:45.910 --> 00:03:47.870 align:middle line:10%
the specialist doctors.

00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:51.710 align:middle line:10%
